Class LynxConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.configuration.LynxConstants

  • public class LynxConstants
extends java.lang.Object
    LynxConstants contains information regarding the configured size of various aspects of a Lynx module.

      • getControlHubVersion

        public static int getControlHubVersion()
        Returns the version of the Control Hub for the purpose of identifying software compatibility. Increasing the CH version number in the OS means that new versions of the SDK and AP service will need to be released. Specifically, AndroidBoard.getInstance must be modified to support the new version number, and the value of the `org.firstinspires.latestSupportedControlHubVersion` meta-data tag in the manifests must be increased.

      • getControlHubOsVersion

        public static java.lang.String getControlHubOsVersion()
        Get the Control Hub OS version. Returns null if OS version property is not set. Value is human-readable, do not attempt to parse. Use getControlHubOsVersionNum() ()} to differentiate between OS versions programmatically.
